data: Start with a short flashforward with Mikoto leading in Tour de France. Back to the present, Mikoto uses his own money to buy food for some upperclassmen during break. Meets his crush Yuki after school. She tries to convince him to join the cycling club. He's flattered but still unsure. Then he asks her to model for his drawing. He gets caught up in the moment and goes out of control, jumping up on the school desk, which reminds Yuki about her brother Yôsuke. Yuki later throws the painting through the window because Mikoto had drawn her wearing a bikini.

data: After being tired of small toy foxes, Augie looks into the woods for a real one.
Augie is permitted by his father to guard their home for one night.
Augie befriends a skunk, much to his father's dislike.
An ant takes a beating from Doggie Daddy, then decides to assemble some troops to get back at him.
Augie comes up with a flying saucer and heads into orbit.
Augie wants to keep a horse at home but his father is reluctant.

Three mosquitoes infiltrate the duo's home.

Doggie Daddy makes up stories about him being one of the musketeers just to impress his child.
Doggie Daddy receives a horse for birthday.
Augie makes up an imaginary friend.
Doggie Daddy plans to make a real genius out of his son.
Augie and a British parrot went on treasure hunting.
Augie befriends a gorilla and tries to keep it indoors.
Augie starts to go on a journey on his own.
Augie gets his hands on a money-counterfeiting machine. The owner attempts to get it back from him.
Doggie Daddy gives pointers to Augie on how to impress the guests at the party.
Doggie Daddy wants the Scottish mouse to leave the house but it refuses.
The family goes on a hunting trip to Mars, encountering a wacky Martian "rabbit".
